“I turn my body from the sun. What ho, Tashtego! let me hear thy hammer. Oh! 
ye three unsurrendered spires of mine; thou uncracked keel; and only 
god-bullied hull; thou firm deck, and haughty helm, and Pole-pointed 
prow,—death-glorious ship! must ye then perish, and without me? Am I cut off 
from the last fond pride of meanest shipwrecked captains? Oh, lonely death on 
